                            <comment id="66474" author="luke" created="Tue, 17 May 2011 02:40:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Support for an AuthenticationSuccessHandler has already been added (&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-1603&quot; title=&quot;Add authentication-success-handler-ref attribute to &amp;lt;remember-me&amp;gt; tag&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SEC-1603&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SEC-1603&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;), but a failure handlder doesn&apos;t make much sense, since the normal pattern would be to fall through and make the user log in.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You would be better using an event listener for logging authentication information.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
